The number of recruits from Ukraine preparing to be sent to Donbass is announced
The official representative of the People's Police of the self-proclaimed Lugansk People's Republic (LNR) Andrei Marochko said that in the winter of 2018-2019 Ukraine will send to Donbass at least 3 thousand recruits.
According to him, in this way Kiev plans "at least somehow to complete the units".
"The unwillingness of citizens of Ukraine to serve in the Armed Forces of Ukraine, mass layoffs led to a low staffing of units", - said Marochko, who is quoted by RIA Novosti.
He also did not rule out that the real numbers of Ukrainians conscripted to the army can be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev launched the so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by the United Forces operation (OOS).
It was assumed that this measure would strengthen the role of the Ukrainian security forces in the settlement of the situation.
At the end of August 2018, the situation in Donbass escalated due to the murder of the head of the Donetsk People's Republic Alexander Zakharchenko.
The authorities of the Donetsk People's Republic qualified the incident as a terrorist attack.
During the investigation of the criminal case, several people involved in the explosion were detained.
According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the sabotage was organized by the Ukrainian special services.
U.S. authorities forced Musk to leave the post of chairman of the board of Tesla
American businessman Ilon Musk will leave the post of chairman of the board of directors of the company founded by him Tesla at the request of the U.S. authorities.
To settle the claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $20 million.
According to CNBC, the pre-trial agreement with the agency allows Musk to remain in the leadership position in Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $20 million and leave the post of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and for at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed to his place.
It is specified that the agreement should still be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission accused Musk of misleading shareholders with a statement of sufficient funds to buy back shares of this company and sued the entrepreneur.
It is about the publication of a businessman on Twitter, where he said he wanted to buy shares of Tesla at $420 per piece, but did not do so.
After the tweet, the company's shares rose by almost 11%.
British Foreign Minister compared the EU with the Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Minister Jeremy Hunt compared the EU to the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of capturing the member states of the community.
The diplomat made this statement at the congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
As noted by the Daily Mail, thus Hunt commented on the difficulties in the negotiation process on Brexit.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to protect freedom, and the Soviet Union did not allow anyone to leave it.
The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from community to prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who wants to escape from captivity ", - said the minister.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the EU will only exacerbate the crisis, said "Gazeta.ru".
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said that the Brexit negotiations had reached a deadlock.
So she commented on the results of the informal EU summit in Salzburg.
The decision to Brexit was taken in 2016 after a referendum.
The United Kingdom's withdrawal is expected to take place before April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by many factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
In addition, the issue of the Irish border remains open.
