In Indonesia, more than 100 prisoners escaped from prison after earthquake
More than 100 prisoners escaped from prison in the Indonesian province of Central Sulawesi.
The escape was possible after two powerful earthquakes on the island of magnitude 7.2 and 7.4.
According to The Jakarta Post, the incident occurred on September 28, when detainees in Palu prison demanded their release in connection with the tremors.
More than 340 prisoners staged a riot and set the institution on fire.
The police who arrived at the place of emergency partially took control of the situation, but more than 100 people escaped from prison.
The building itself was seriously damaged and the guards struggled to detain the prisoners.
The number of victims of the earthquake and tsunami that occurred on Sulawesi Island increased to 832 people.
Due to this, it is still not possible to establish transport links, electricity and communication with some areas of the island.
"Golden Pearl" for "extreme realism"
For the third time in history, the San Sebastian International Film Festival has recognized the Spanish film as the best film of the year.
The main award - "Golden Shell" - was awarded to the drama "Between Two Seas" directed by Isaki Lakuesta.
This film with almost documentary realism tells the difficult story of the life of two brothers in the Spanish seaside province of Cadiz - Lacuesta presented the continuation of his 2006 film "The Legend of Time".
At the award ceremony of the film festival in San Sebastian, the creators of the Argentine thriller "Red", which was awarded in several nominations, were honored.
Benjamin Naystat was declared the director of the year, Pedro Sotero was awarded for his camera work, and Dario Grandinetti was recognized as the best actor.
Pia Tielta from Norway became the actress of the year at the San Sebastian Film Festival.
The jury highly appreciated her participation in the film "Blind Spot" - a drama about the life of one family after the attempted suicide of her daughter.
The film became the director's debut of the Swedish actress Tuva Novotny.
In the nomination "Best Screenplay" the victory was shared by the films "Julia" and "Faithful Man".
The special prize of the jury was awarded to the Philippine criminal drama "Alpha: the right to murder".
Vertigo, tears and laughter
The festival in San Sebastian is called one of the main cultural events in Spain and one of the most important European film competitions.
The owner of the "Golden Shell" director Isaki Lakuesta told about his impressions of the festival Euronews:
It was wonderful!
We came here all team and of course we experienced dizzying moments, tears, laughter.
We are happy.
This film we started to prepare 14 years ago, it was a very long work, and what is especially important for me is that we did not want to stop.
Now is the time of joy and gratitude.
As noted by Euronews correspondent Carlos Marlaska, Isaki Lacuesta's film organically fits into the collection of paintings that received "Golden shells", but the festival in San Sebastian did not do without unexpected, sometimes shocking decisions of the jury, which sometimes even call the calling card of the competition ".
