At the same time, the group opposed Germany's "sponsorship" of weak EU economies, did not rule out the possibility of a return to the German mark and a complete withdrawal from the EU.
Against the background of the deepening immigration crisis, the AfD's political platform has expanded.
In 2013, the group formed a full-fledged party that took the niche of Euroskeptics and began to criticize the government harshly for the failure of immigration policy.
