Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic increasingly visit the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiffs Service of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational - control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months more than 140 thousand visits to the site were registered, more than 42 thousand - the section "Data Bank of executive proceedings", 661 payment receipts on payment of debts were downloaded.
According to the chairman of the Public Council under the UFSSP of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan Valery Bogdanov, almost every resident of the region registered debts for utility payments, fines traffic police, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
But debtors may face negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on travel abroad.
That is why UFSSP Russia in Kazakhstan recommends all who planned a trip abroad, to clarify in the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the site www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service has created a "Data Bank of enforcement proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is not only on regional sites UFSSP Russia, but also in social networks and mobile phones iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The database contains information about the enforcement proceedings initiated by Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains the assistant head of the UFSSP of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan Delgir Bodgaeva.
"In the presence of debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive sheet or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the department of bailiffs; the name of the bailiff; contact phone.
