Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation predicted the ruble exchange rate for 17 years ahead
The Ministry of Finance of Russia expects a gradual depreciation of the ruble exchange rate - up to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025, the ruble exchange rate, according to the forecast, will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles, and in the next five years - 73.9 rubles.
The Office notes that these figures are a nominal rate.
The real effective exchange rate (the indicator taking into account the changes in the exchange rates of the countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assure.
As for inflation, until 2020 it will be 3.5%, and then stabilize at the level of about 4%, the Ministry of Finance believes.
